Dollar Exchange Rates from 2004 to 2020 by month

graph1 <- ggplot(data=dollarexchange, aes(x=Months, y=Exchangerate)) 
graph1 + geom_line(color='blue')

Line Chart of Dollar Exchange Rates

This graph shows us that the USD Dollar has gradually gained value according to TL. While a relatively stable graph can be observed between 2002 and 2010, a serious increase has been observed especially after 2010 (After the 100th month). We can say that the increase rate has peaked in the last 3 years. There could be many reasons for this situation, but the most important of these is economic instability and lack of confidence in the economy.

The graphic below gives us the figures of the last 4 years.

ggplot(data=tail(dollarexchange,30), aes(x=Months, y=Exchangerate)) + geom_line()

Last 4 year Exchange Rates
